      • keepAlive

        public boolean keepAlive()
        Returns true if and only if the connection can remain open and thus 'kept alive'. This methods respects the value of the "Connection" header first and if this has no such header then the keep-alive status is determined by the HTTP version, that is, HTTP/1.1 is keep-alive by default, HTTP/1.0 is not keep-alive by default.
        Returns:
        true if the connection is keep-alive
